{
  "texts": [
    "Notably, each node utilizes a distinct LSTM, though the weights can be shared.",
    "The difference between WD-GCN and CD-GCN is that CD-GCN adds skip connections to GCN.RNNs are not the only available option for learning time series.",
    "In recent studies, GNNs have also been used in combination with other kinds of deep time series models.",
    "For instance, DySAT [37] introduces a stacked architecture made up entirely of self-attention blocks.",
    "They use attention mechanisms in both the spatial and temporal dimensions, employing Graph Attention Networks (GAT) [30] for the spatial dimension and Transformers [14] for the temporal dimension."
  ]
}